$ System.IntPtr (struct)

`System.IntPtr` represents a handle or a pointer.

The size (number of bits) of `System.IntPtr` corresponds to the bitness of the operating system that PowerShell runs on.
Thus, it is useful to determine the running executable's bitness, such
as demonstrated → Windows/PowerShell#ps-32-64[here].

sa:
  → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/_integral-numeric-types
